The paper deals with the layout of graphs, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of stacks and queues suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The study of mixed layouts and subdivisions involves graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the application of these concepts to planar graphs suggests a connection to computational complexity and algorithms (cs.SI).
